					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-728481#post-1895502</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-728481/scp-1493#post-1895502</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 18 Nov 2013 12:54:43 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Drewbear</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>301632</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Something I've had to correct people about before: it's physically impossible for sound more than 196.something or 197.something dB to be transmitted via air. From my understanding, at that volume the troughs of the sound waves are literally in vacuum.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
